            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I don't think we need an `on_error` callback, we can make the iterator return a third value `err`, which is used like this:\n\n```lua\nfor name, type, err in vim.fs.dir(path, { depth = math.huge }) do\n  if err ~= nil then\n    -- Handle error\n  end\nend\n```\n\nFor use cases that don't care about errors (or that do want to treat an error as equivalent to \"empty\"), you can just omit the `err` from the loop.",
