        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Hey, I am interested to work on this. I like @gpanders suggestion, however there is an additional case. If the base directory (the `path` supplied) is an un-readable directory (lacking permissions, doesn't exist) how would we convey the error in that case? \nIn the current implementation, if that happens, it returns an empty Iterator which would be equivalent to an empty directory.\nWith the iterator based error handling, sub-directory errors can be surfaced through err, but the root directory failure would have to be handled separately. ",
